    Contains the pre messages for each SBMLError in the English language.

    'pre' mean that this is added at the beginning of the generic error message defined in the SBMLErrorMessage bundle. This part of the error is, in general, a disclaimer about the error, for example, when an error is reported for an SBML level and version where it was not existing initially.

    The key for each pre message is the integer defined for each SBMLError in SBMLErrorCodes.
